exercise.p:
Suppose you are trying to factor a quadratic that has the following condition:

	\left\{
		\begin{array}{l}
			\text{Multiply to a positive number} \\
			\text{Add to a positive number}
		\end{array}
		\right.
				
What information can you conclude about the signs of the two numbers you're looking for?

Suppose you are trying to factor a quadratic that has the following condition:

	\left\{
		\begin{array}{l}
			\text{Multiply to a positive number} \\
			\text{Add to a negative number}
		\end{array}
		\right.

What information can you conclude about the signs of the two numbers you're looking for?

Suppose you are trying to factor a quadratic that has the following condition:

	\left\{
		\begin{array}{l}
			\text{Multiply to a negative number} \\
			\text{Add to a positive number}
		\end{array}
		\right.

What information can you conclude about the signs of the two numbers you're looking for?

